Nutrition for children suffering from obesity: No breakfast and sausage for dinner
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 weigh more than normal; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% are obese.
According to the latest study, children suffering from obesity usually come from families leading an unhealthy lifestyle.
Once again, we see the importance of the environment and the behaviors that accompany a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausage appears on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children who have a normal weight.
More than 19% of obese children ate French fries for dinner on the eve of a survey related to an educational event called Obesity is not an accident.
Moreover, families of children suffering from obesity do not engage in sports. This, however, applies to most families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said that their parents find time for sports at least once a week.
The study included 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of last academic year and involved nearly 900 elementary school students across Bohemia.
The Obesity event was not an accident held for the second year in a row, with the support of the insurance company V<0xC5><0xA1>eobecná zdravstvo poji<0xC5><0xA1>t'ovna and the company Unilever.
To date, more than 12 thousand schoolchildren-students of grades 4-8 have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and sufficient exercise are the main determining factors causing a rapidly growing number of children who suffer from either overweight or obesity.
“For example, only half of the respondents said that they eat five times a day, according to the scheme of breakfast-snack-lunch-snack-dinner, and this is one of the indispensable conditions for proper nutrition,” says one of the conclusions of the study.
No lunch and no sausage in the evenings.
Experts warn that even such relative details as the constant time of a family breakfast are important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of school children eat breakfast together.
Most families eat breakfast separately.
The worst discovery was that in every tenth family people do not eat breakfast at all.
And yet breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study showed that fried food is more often consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sugary soft drinks every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children regularly play sports, this figure is reduced by more than half - up to 15% - when it comes to their parents.
Make your own menu.
In another part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the products offered and based on their tastes and preferences.
“Food preferences in Czech children aged 12-15 are far from ideal when it comes to healthy eating.”
Their favorite food includes a large number of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
“The great popularity of sugary soft drinks is a particular concern,” the study concluded.
As the main lunch dish, the pasta defeated the bird with a slight advantage.
However, the children showed little interest in legumes, fish and vegetable dishes.
Striving for a healthy lifestyle
The study also found that children are willing to change their eating habits provided they are provided with relevant information.
“Many participants in the control group of the study showed a significant shift in preferences towards healthy food when filling out the questionnaire after the end of the lecture Obesity is not an accident,” says the project results.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sugary soft drinks - more children began to prefer them just water.
In addition, as the main dish, children more often noted poultry and fish, limiting the number of sweet dishes and pastries.
A stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article about training for stylists, I complained about the amount of information in the introductory classes.
I had no idea what was going to happen next.
Lectures by three experts in the field; advice on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a seminar on how it all works in real life.
Further - more.
The closer we are to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
The training takes place every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, (there is not a single man on the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
One has a short neck, the other has a boyish figure without proper shapes, another weighs more than the norm.
The stylist should know how to visually reduce the wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or add the missing volumes.
We were given advice on how to emphasize the figure of such women as Jennifer Lopez, i.e. the owners of a more lush chest and thighs and a narrow waist, and at the same time not to dress them too provocatively.
For example, if the difference in the volume of the waist and hips is so large that you can not pick up a skirt or trousers, it is worth having at least one thing sewn to order.
You will definitely not regret the invested funds, because ideally sitting clothes are priceless.
In a skirt made to order, you will feel much better than in one that constantly moves, rolls, exposes the waist, etc.
Holders of boyish figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with ruffles, appliques, embroidery or folds.
Given the abundance of such information and types of figures, I am glad that I have a whole week to realize all this.
And yet, I'm afraid it's too much, given the homework we've been given.
Each participant of the course had to come up with two outfits for a celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We must take into account their modern appearance, their style in clothes and the type of figure.
I have to dress Miranda Kerr, which you may know from Victoria's Secret advertising campaigns.
I’m happy for myself, because it’s much easier to dress her than, say, Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who recently recovered a ton (please keep in mind that I’m exaggerating), or the very young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut clothes out of magazines or find them on the Internet, print and process them using graphic programs.
The Mudboard - so called the result of the work - then reflects our own style and attitude to the graphic image.
It is important to keep in mind the graphic component of the style.
The stylist does not just dress real people, but creates product pages in magazines (based on special instructions, for example, fashion bags, coats, etc.).
This is what the stylist and designer Mario Kamenik told us about.
But that was only on Sunday.
Stylists need general knowledge.
Saturday's lecture, full of information about the types of figures, was revived by three guests - specialists in this field.
Stylist, Honza Pokorny; fashion designer, Jakub Polanka; and fashion photographer Ben Rench.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should use this fact.
A good stylist knows how to use one item of clothing in different ways.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a trench coat can be worn in the usual way, over jeans and T-shirts, like a coat; but it can also be worn on a naked body, without fasteners, like a dress.
Another option is to roll up your sleeves or raise your collar, and the whole image changes completely.
“Play with him,” he said.
Anyway, I appreciated the following advice most of all: "For your work, you need to know the rules perfectly."
Then you can start breaking them,” Jacob told us.
Here I finally understood why we collect all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see quite another.
Not to mention fashion shows.
From Ben, a photographer, I learned that a stylist should have more outfit options than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a fashion review on ten pages (equivalent to ten outfits), I have to be ready to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that in the picture, the item of clothing often looks and works in combination with others quite differently than in reality.
We have to keep this in mind when we create an image.
Honza Pokorny confirmed that often the image and style is half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who doesn’t have amazing vocals, but her image and marketing have made her a global star.
The attitude to the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even well-known people often think this is unnecessary (and believe that it is enough to be an expert in something, and the way they look is secondary).
And if someone finally allows us to create their style, we should expect them to name us a different (smaller) size than the one they actually wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids wrote anything about the fact that some celebrity has lost weight / lost weight, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario emphasized that it is not enough for a stylist to understand fashion and be able to pick up an outfit.
Our work mainly consists of communicating with the people we dress; therefore, it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to evaluate people, not to condone them and stick to their opinions.
“If a manager asks you to look at her clothes and add a few nice things, you can’t throw away her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are terrible.”
“Find at least a few things you can praise and advise what you can wear with them,” says Mario.
He also showed us exactly what a work bag should fit.
This is a bag that you tie around your waist to carry everything you need.
In addition to the obvious things, such as scissors, a sticky roller or English pins, it should have a nylon thread (stylists use it when shooting some items, for example, a bag or hat), special clips to fasten the fabric on the back in case the clothes are too large (pencils and similar items are prohibited because they spoil the clothes) or a set.
To distract from the lectures and get some practical experience, we learned how to make linings on the soles of shoes.
Even when shooting in a studio where the floor is smooth, the soles can get damaged – not to mention shooting outdoors.
So, we got into gluing.
You should not touch the shoes with scissors, so as not to spoil them.
This requires real skill.
I was glad that Mario praised my work.
These skills did not appeal to me.
This is only part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend courses.
I’m starting to realize that being a professional stylist isn’t as easy as it sounds.
V Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
<0xD0><0xA1>ompany
What was supposed to be a carefree walk turned into a routine morning commute due to a series of completely inappropriate and careless mistakes.
The ambitions were met to a certain extent, but it didn’t matter, because no one clearly wanted to do extra work.
Before the release of the new version with the subtitle "Escape" associated with high hopes.
It was expected to move the previous Need For Speed series in a new direction; demo versions indicated that the game would take a worthy place in the racing game genre.
We were curious to see the parts of the game where the protagonist gets out of the car and runs away.
As is often the case with NFS, the end result is very different from what we expected.
The game is a pretty good arcade race, but the overall impression is spoiled by a few unnecessary mistakes that have been present in this series of games for several years.
So, in fact, these are not mistakes, but a manifestation of inexplicable laziness of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You become part of a story, the main character of which, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You get in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get to New York first.
This idea has several interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race takes place on its own route, individual stages take place in a diverse and interesting environment.
It doesn’t feel like the same thing is happening in the game all the time.
Despite the fact that the graphics are at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some tracks are nice to look at.
And yet the game does not cause strong emotions.
Although driving through the desert, in the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the race is revived from time to time by an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to fall under an avalanche.
The individual races are pretty well organized.
There are only a few varieties, but that’s enough.
For a while you try to outrun a few opponents (essentially a regular race); then you try to improve time (a standard race with a stopwatch); or you compete against one opponent.
Among other things, you occasionally run into the police, which further complicates your task.
The components on the outside of the car are new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
It's not complicated.
Although surprisingly, these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (only three to be exact).
In fact, it turns out to be good for the game, because this property is not boring; given all of the above, it is one of the things that make the game more entertaining.
The racing model follows in the footsteps of previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you are looking for an imitation of real life, you will have to look elsewhere.
And yet this driving model is very suitable for dynamic racing, although you can find better options on the market.
So far, so good.
After a while, however, the problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
From such a game do not expect complex transformations and collisions, but if you have no idea before the collision with the object, how your car will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, overtaking or passing cars in a dense stream, you sometimes slightly touch another car. And yet sometimes in a practically similar situation, your car begins to spin furiously.
Or smashed to bits.
This is not so important thanks to the restart system, but it is enough to spoil the fun.
The restarts are arranged so that if you break or go far away from the track, the game returns you to the point where it was interrupted.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful in case something doesn’t work out, but you can’t fully rely on it.
Sometimes restarts are not enough, and you have to memorize a separate section of the race.
An important disadvantage of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to be made in a certain way, otherwise you simply will not fit in.
In other cases, you meet civilian cars in a certain place in the same configuration regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see your opponent easily passing between two cars moving in the opposite direction, whereas when you get there, the cars are already positioned so that you either need to go around them or slow down.
It doesn’t matter when you’re around them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens right in front of your nose.
Rivals have other advantages.
During the game you discover several places where, regardless of the time, the same opponent overtakes you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on a long bridge where you drive in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent has to stand up to you no matter what.
The fact is that when it drives in front of you, it degrades your view, leading to one or more accidents at that site.
You can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and filled with adrenaline, but it is so obvious that it quickly begins to cause irritation.
Too bad, because despite the simple driving model, the game is entertaining and sometimes so eventful that you do not have time to pay attention to what is happening around you.
It doesn’t matter what doesn’t make you bored – a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
You need to track the filling stations along the way, because it is on them that your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
Machines are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars for straight stretches of highway; and exotic super-athletes for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain trails.
The main story mode is closely related to the challenge mode; it is a race on individual sections that you will learn as the game progresses.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and points common to the challenges and story modes.
Many options are available for obtaining a higher level of driving: from cars to profile data.
In addition, the profile is associated with the online Autolog function, which, among other things, compares the results you have achieved with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here’s another flaw that’s hard to understand; it’s an example from the last race in a row.
You and your car get into a subway tunnel (we’ll assume so) where you’re racing on rails in the dark (we’ll assume so).
Your speedometer shows the figures from 150 to 200 km/h (let’s assume so), when suddenly a subway train flies at you from behind, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
For several days, our editors discussed whether no one really thought for a second during the creation of the game, or its creators really consider us such fools.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video sequence is mostly pleasant, sometimes even stunning.
Although it is a pity that in some critical moments the quality of recording, sometimes quite strongly, decreases.
This is especially true for events with a large number of participants, where a good record would not help you much either.
The sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the amateur.
To cater to as wide a youth audience as possible, the soundtrack 'included compositions from different styles'; but it is unlikely that many people will buy the game because of its music.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: Escape is pretty messy.
If the game had avoided clearly unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of the NFS over the past few years.
Either way, the game leaves a feeling of incompleteness.
Of course, this is good entertainment, but be prepared for the fact that the shortcomings will blind you as an airport searchlight.
