But the two largest Swiss banks, UBS and Credit Suisse, at some point gave up Swiss notions of banking — or, as the head of one of the small Swiss banks believes, betrayed them.
He wouldn’t want to see his name in the paper – like all Swiss bankers, he also cooperates with the two largest banks.
He believes that UBS has become too big – in particular, in investment banking, where Anglo-Saxons are very active.
