Jurgens also expressed her opinion about complaints about the noise made by birds. "Noise conveys a lot of information. They have a lot to say to each other."
The mind and ingenuity of these birds have entered the legends. Gracchi often not only use tools to capture the bit that they like, but also make the tools themselves.
Behavioral researchers at the University of Cambridge recently tested a measure of a bird’s mind on four peas.
In one experiment, the birds quickly realized that you need to knock on the board to get a moth larva.
