Thus, a partial recount of one or more ballot boxes may be made on the condition that: the results of the protocols do not coincide; there is no voting and counting protocol in the ballot box or it is not with the chairman; or when there are obvious errors or corrections in the protocol.
In addition, a total recount of votes in all ballot boxes in an election may take place when there is a sign that the difference between the proposed candidate winning the election in question and the one who received the second place in the voting is less than or equal to one percent, provided that at the beginning of the session there is a request from a representative of the party and/or coalition that nominated the second of those candidates.
A total recount shall also be made if, at the end of the regular recount, it is established that the difference between the winner and the candidate in second place is less than or equal to one per cent, provided that there is a request from the political party whose candidate has taken second place, in the event that the ballot boxes that were counted in the partial recount are excluded.
